[2026-03-08T04:28:16Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019C3qYQfCo7PwbDmGC6UZuV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package dsl\n     2→\n     3→type TokenType int\n     4→\n     5→const (\n     6→\tTokenEOF     TokenType = iota\n     7→\tTokenIllegal\n     8→\tTokenIdent\n     9→\tTokenString\n    10→\tTokenLBrace\n    11→\tTokenRBrace\n    12→\tTokenLBracket\n    13→\tTokenRBracket\n    14→\tTokenLParen\n    15→\tTokenRParen\n    16→\tTokenComma\n    17→\tTokenEquals\n    18→\tTokenArrow\n    19→\tTokenColon\n    20→\tTokenDot\n    21→)\n    22→\n    23→func (t TokenType) String() string {\n    24→\tswitch t {\n    25→\tcase TokenEOF:\n    26→\t\treturn \"EOF\"\n    27→\tcase TokenIllegal:\n    28→\t\treturn \"ILLEGAL\"\n    29→\tcase TokenIdent:\n    30→\t\treturn \"IDENT\"\n    31→\tcase TokenString:\n    32→\t\treturn \"STRING\"\n    33→\tcase TokenLBrace:\n    34→\t\treturn \"LBRACE\"\n    35→\tcase TokenRBrace:\n    36→\t\treturn \"RBRACE\"\n    37→\tcase TokenLBracket:\n    38→\t\treturn \"LBRACKET\"\n    39→\tcase TokenRBracket:\n    40→\t\treturn \"RBRACKET\"\n    41→\tcase TokenLParen:\n    42→\t\treturn \"LPAREN\"\n    43→\tcase TokenRParen:\n    44→\t\treturn \"RPAREN\"\n    45→\tcase TokenComma:\n    46→\t\treturn \"COMMA\"\n    47→\tcase TokenEquals:\n    48→\t\treturn \"EQUALS\"\n    49→\tcase TokenArrow:\n    50→\t\treturn \"ARROW\"\n    51→\tcase TokenColon:\n    52→\t\treturn \"COLON\"\n    53→\tcase TokenDot:\n    54→\t\treturn \"DOT\"\n    55→\tdefault:\n    56→\t\treturn \"UNKNOWN\"\n    57→\t}\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→type Token struct {\n    61→\tType    TokenType\n    62→\tLiteral string\n    63→\tLine    int\n    64→\tCol     int\n    65→}\n    66→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019atLhmsCs71sLWrnt284jZ","session_id":"f2e3b2d0-9fec-45ae-be26-9ef919219ac8","uuid":"8299a73d-0458-487c-85e9-0ab183a60c95"}
[2026-03-08T04:28:16Z] [llm] {"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a3d5037b6e1d8ebdc","tool_use_id":"toolu_019atLhmsCs71sLWrnt284jZ","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore DSL parser config","usage":{"total_tokens":29958,"tool_uses":13,"duration_ms":24829},"uuid":"3a2afe98-8615-4849-970c-86715ecdde7d","session_id":"f2e3b2d0-9fec-45ae-be26-9ef919219ac8"}
[2026-03-08T04:28:16Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019atLhmsCs71sLWrnt284jZ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the key findings:\n\n## Summary: DSL Parser and Step Config Storage\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the DSL parser in `internal/dsl/` and examined multiple `.cloche` workflow files. Here's what I found about how step configs are stored:\n\n### Core Data Structures\n\n**Step struct** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 21-26):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n\tName    string\n\tType    StepType\n\tResults []string\n\tConfig  map[string]string  // THIS IS THE KEY MAP\n}\n```\n\n**StepType enum** (lines 13-19):\n- `StepTypeAgent` — steps with `prompt` config\n- `StepTypeScript` — steps with `run` config  \n- `StepTypeWorkflow` — steps with `workflow_name` config\n\n### What Values End Up in `step.Config`\n\n#### 1. **step.Config[\"prompt\"]** — Agent Steps\n\nWhen a step has a `prompt` field, the parser stores the prompt value directly as a string:\n\n- **Plain string**: `prompt = \"do something\"` → stores `\"do something\"`\n- **File function**: `prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` → stores `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` (literal string, not evaluated)\n\n**Parser code** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, lines 298-342, `parseValue()`):\n- Strings are stored as-is\n- Function calls like `file(...)` are reconstructed as literal strings: `file(\"path\")`\n- Dotted paths like `step.code.output` are supported and stored as dotted identifiers\n\n**Examples from workflows**:\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` line 3: `prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` → stores `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/develop.cloche` line 3: `prompt = file(\"prompts/design.md\")` → stores `file(\"prompts/design.md\")`\n\n#### 2. **step.Config[\"run\"]** — Script Steps\n\nWhen a step has a `run` field, the entire shell command is stored as a string:\n\n- Shell commands with pipes, redirection, etc. are stored verbatim\n- Can be multi-command strings with `&&`, `||`, pipes\n\n**Examples**:\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` line 8: `run = \"go test ./... 2>&1\"` → stores `\"go test ./... 2>&1\"`\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/develop.cloche` line 13: `run = \"make clean && make test 2>&1\"` → stores that exact string\n- `/workspace/examples/hello-world/build.cloche` line 3: `run = \"echo 'Initializing project...' && mkdir -p src dist\"` → stores the exact command\n\n#### 3. **step.Config[\"workflow_name\"]** — Nested Workflow Steps\n\nWhen a step references another workflow, the workflow name is stored:\n\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` line 8: `workflow_name = \"develop\"` → stores `\"develop\"`\n\n**Parser test example** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`, lines 250-252):\n```\nstep develop {\n  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n  results       = [success, fail]\n}\n```\nStored as: `develop.Config[\"workflow_name\"] = \"develop\"`\n\n### Step Type Inference Logic\n\n**Parser code** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, lines 166-195):\n\nThe parser automatically infers the step type by checking which config key is present:\n\n```go\nhasPrompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"] != \"\"\nhasRun := step.Config[\"run\"] != \"\"\nhasWorkflowName := step.Config[\"workflow_name\"] != \"\"\n\nif hasPrompt:\n    step.Type = domain.StepTypeAgent\nelse if hasRun:\n    step.Type = domain.StepTypeScript\nelse if hasWorkflowName:\n    step.Type = domain.StepTypeWorkflow\n```\n\nA step must have **exactly one** of these three keys, or parsing fails.\n\n### Other Step Config Keys\n\nSteps can also store these recognized keys in `step.Config` (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 135-146):\n\n- **`max_attempts`**: retry limit (e.g., `\"2\"`)\n- **`timeout`**: execution timeout\n- **`agent_command`**: override agent binary\n- **`agent_args`**: agent-specific arguments\n- **`results`**: declared result names (stored in `step.Results[]` not Config)\n- **`feedback`**: feedback to agent\n- **`prompt_step`**: reference to a prior step for context\n\n### Container Configuration\n\nContainer settings use a dot-notation prefix in `step.Config`:\n\n**Parser code** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, lines 200-221):\nWhen parsing nested blocks like:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = \"do something\"\n  container {\n    image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"internal.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success]\n}\n```\n\nThe container fields are stored with `container.` prefix:\n- `step.Config[\"container.image\"] = \"cloche/agent:latest\"`\n- `step.Config[\"container.network_allow\"] = \"docs.python.org,internal.example.com\"` (comma-joined)\n\n**Parser test** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`, lines 76-95):\n```go\nassert.Equal(t, \"cloche/agent:latest\", code.Config[\"container.image\"])\nassert.Equal(t, \"docs.python.org,internal.example.com\", code.Config[\"container.network_allow\"])\n```\n\n### Key Files for Reference\n\n- **Parser**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` — Lines 139-248 contain the step parsing logic\n- **Domain types**: `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` — Step struct definition\n- **Parser tests**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go` — 361 lines of comprehensive test cases\n- **Example workflows**: \n  - `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` — Mix of agent (prompt) and script (run) steps\n  - `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` — Demonstrates nested workflow_name steps\n  - `/workspace/testdata/workflows/simple.cloche` — Minimal script-only example"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3d5037b6e1d8ebdc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31518\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 24835</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f2e3b2d0-9fec-45ae-be26-9ef919219ac8","uuid":"a2c70622-7ec6-4593-87aa-91e2c3d8a8ad","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Look at the DSL parser in internal/dsl/ to understand how step configs (prompt, run, script) are stored. I need to understand what values end up in step.Config[\"prompt\"], step.Config[\"run\"], and step.Config[\"script\"]. Also look at any .cloche workflow files (*.cloche) to see examples. Be thorough - show relevant code.","agentId":"a3d5037b6e1d8ebdc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the key findings:\n\n## Summary: DSL Parser and Step Config Storage\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the DSL parser in `internal/dsl/` and examined multiple `.cloche` workflow files. Here's what I found about how step configs are stored:\n\n### Core Data Structures\n\n**Step struct** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 21-26):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n\tName    string\n\tType    StepType\n\tResults []string\n\tConfig  map[string]string  // THIS IS THE KEY MAP\n}\n```\n\n**StepType enum** (lines 13-19):\n- `StepTypeAgent` — steps with `prompt` config\n- `StepTypeScript` — steps with `run` config  \n- `StepTypeWorkflow` — steps with `workflow_name` config\n\n### What Values End Up in `step.Config`\n\n#### 1. **step.Config[\"prompt\"]** — Agent Steps\n\nWhen a step has a `prompt` field, the parser stores the prompt value directly as a string:\n\n- **Plain string**: `prompt = \"do something\"` → stores `\"do something\"`\n- **File function**: `prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` → stores `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` (literal string, not evaluated)\n\n**Parser code** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, lines 298-342, `parseValue()`):\n- Strings are stored as-is\n- Function calls like `file(...)` are reconstructed as literal strings: `file(\"path\")`\n- Dotted paths like `step.code.output` are supported and stored as dotted identifiers\n\n**Examples from workflows**:\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` line 3: `prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` → stores `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/develop.cloche` line 3: `prompt = file(\"prompts/design.md\")` → stores `file(\"prompts/design.md\")`\n\n#### 2. **step.Config[\"run\"]** — Script Steps\n\nWhen a step has a `run` field, the entire shell command is stored as a string:\n\n- Shell commands with pipes, redirection, etc. are stored verbatim\n- Can be multi-command strings with `&&`, `||`, pipes\n\n**Examples**:\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` line 8: `run = \"go test ./... 2>&1\"` → stores `\"go test ./... 2>&1\"`\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/develop.cloche` line 13: `run = \"make clean && make test 2>&1\"` → stores that exact string\n- `/workspace/examples/hello-world/build.cloche` line 3: `run = \"echo 'Initializing project...' && mkdir -p src dist\"` → stores the exact command\n\n#### 3. **step.Config[\"workflow_name\"]** — Nested Workflow Steps\n\nWhen a step references another workflow, the workflow name is stored:\n\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` line 8: `workflow_name = \"develop\"` → stores `\"develop\"`\n\n**Parser test example** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`, lines 250-252):\n```\nstep develop {\n  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n  results       = [success, fail]\n}\n```\nStored as: `develop.Config[\"workflow_name\"] = \"develop\"`\n\n### Step Type Inference Logic\n\n**Parser code** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, lines 166-195):\n\nThe parser automatically infers the step type by checking which config key is present:\n\n```go\nhasPrompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"] != \"\"\nhasRun := step.Config[\"run\"] != \"\"\nhasWorkflowName := step.Config[\"workflow_name\"] != \"\"\n\nif hasPrompt:\n    step.Type = domain.StepTypeAgent\nelse if hasRun:\n    step.Type = domain.StepTypeScript\nelse if hasWorkflowName:\n    step.Type = domain.StepTypeWorkflow\n```\n\nA step must have **exactly one** of these three keys, or parsing fails.\n\n### Other Step Config Keys\n\nSteps can also store these recognized keys in `step.Config` (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 135-146):\n\n- **`max_attempts`**: retry limit (e.g., `\"2\"`)\n- **`timeout`**: execution timeout\n- **`agent_command`**: override agent binary\n- **`agent_args`**: agent-specific arguments\n- **`results`**: declared result names (stored in `step.Results[]` not Config)\n- **`feedback`**: feedback to agent\n- **`prompt_step`**: reference to a prior step for context\n\n### Container Configuration\n\nContainer settings use a dot-notation prefix in `step.Config`:\n\n**Parser code** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, lines 200-221):\nWhen parsing nested blocks like:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = \"do something\"\n  container {\n    image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"internal.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success]\n}\n```\n\nThe container fields are stored with `container.` prefix:\n- `step.Config[\"container.image\"] = \"cloche/agent:latest\"`\n- `step.Config[\"container.network_allow\"] = \"docs.python.org,internal.example.com\"` (comma-joined)\n\n**Parser test** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`, lines 76-95):\n```go\nassert.Equal(t, \"cloche/agent:latest\", code.Config[\"container.image\"])\nassert.Equal(t, \"docs.python.org,internal.example.com\", code.Config[\"container.network_allow\"])\n```\n\n### Key Files for Reference\n\n- **Parser**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` — Lines 139-248 contain the step parsing logic\n- **Domain types**: `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` — Step struct definition\n- **Parser tests**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go` — 361 lines of comprehensive test cases\n- **Example workflows**: \n  - `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` — Mix of agent (prompt) and script (run) steps\n  - `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` — Demonstrates nested workflow_name steps\n  - `/workspace/testdata/workflows/simple.cloche` — Minimal script-only example"}],"totalDuratio